{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"9a3c16ae-1d8a-4b18-af82-ff39140d192c","content":"## What happened\n\n`DSA.Create()` throws **`PlatformNotSupportedException`** on macOS because Apple's security frameworks (Security.framework / CryptoKit) have **no native DSA support**. In earlier .NET versions, the runtime provided DSA on macOS via an OpenSSL interop shim, but that fallback has been removed. DSA has been marked `[Obsolete]` (SYSLIB0042) since .NET 7, and the macOS implementation was dropped entirely.\n\n## How to fix it\n\nSince you only need to **verify** legacy signatures (not sign new data), you have two practical options:\n\n### Option 1 — Use BouncyCastle (recommended)\nReplace `System.Security.Cryptography.DSA` with the managed, cross-platform **BouncyCastle** implementation:\n\n```bash\ndotnet add package BouncyCastle.Cryptography\n```\n\n```csharp\nusing Org.BouncyCastle.Crypto.Parameters;\nusing Org.BouncyCastle.Security;\n\nbool VerifyLegacyDsa(byte[] message, byte[] signature, DsaPublicKeyParameters publicKey)\n{\n    var verifier = SignerUtilities.GetSigner(\"SHA-1withDSA\"); // or SHA-256withDSA\n    verifier.Init(forSigning: false, publicKey);\n    verifier.BlockUpdate(message, 0, message.Length);\n    return verifier.VerifySignature(signature);\n}\n```\n\nThis works identically on Linux, Windows, and macOS with no platform-specific code paths.\n\n### Option 2 — Runtime guard + platform split\nIf you want to keep the built-in `DSA` on Windows/Linux and only fall back on macOS:\n\n```csharp\nif (!OperatingSystem.IsMacOS())\n{\n    using var dsa = DSA.Create();\n    // ... existing verification logic\n}\nelse\n{\n    // BouncyCastle path for macOS\n}\n```\n\n### Recommendation\n\nGo with **Option 1** — a single managed implementation across all platforms is simpler to maintain. DSA is a legacy algorithm; once all existing signatures are verified or migrated, plan to move to **Ed25519 / ECDSA**.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"f3fe37cf-bae2-4892-a828-55a0a572c606","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user is asking about a .NET compatibility issue with DSA (Digital Signature Algorithm) on macOS after upgrading from .NET 10 to .NET 11. Let me think about what I know about this topic.\n\nThis is a well-known breaking change in .NET. Starting with .NET 7, Microsoft began deprecating older cryptographic algorithms, and DSA specifically has been affected on macOS.\n\nLet me recall the details:\n\nIn .NET 7, Microsoft made a breaking change where `DSA.Create()` throws `PlatformNotSupportedException` on macOS. This is because macOS (via Apple's Security framework / CommonCrypto) doesn't natively support DSA, and .NET on macOS was using OpenSSL via a compatibility shim. Microsoft decided to remove support for DSA on macOS.\n\n\nThe key issue is that Apple's native cryptographic frameworks don't support DSA, so when .NET stopped relying on OpenSSL for these legacy algorithms on macOS, DSA became unavailable. Since the user is upgrading from .NET 10 to .NET 11, they're likely hitting this breaking change if their code depends on DSA operations. I'm getting clearer on the timeline now. Apple's platforms never had native DSA support in their security frameworks, so .NET on macOS relied on an OpenSSL-based fallback implementation. Microsoft removed that fallback at some point, which is why `DSA.Create()` throws `PlatformNotSupportedException` on macOS in newer .NET versions. The user's scenario of it working on .NET 10 but breaking on .NET 11 aligns with this removal, and the root cause is simply that macOS lacks the underlying DSA support that .NET used to bridge through managed code. The main workarounds are using a library like BouncyCastle if you only need to verify existing DSA signatures, adding platform-specific code paths for macOS, or reconsidering DSA altogether since it's deprecated and considered cryptographically weak. I should give a straightforward answer about this breaking change without overcomplicating it.","outputTokens":1706,"requestId":"3009:6BA82:161688B:18D7369:6A067BC7"},"id":"60c5c115-0a4c-4739-8018-c1219354f670","timestamp":"2026-05-15T01:50:35.771Z","parentId":"0d054515-bfe1-4d1d-b628-cda773e5ac01"}
